description.narrative:
Diakonia's overall goal and expected long-term change/impact with the SAP-II is to improve quality of life of communities (specifically women, youth, the poor and most vulnerable groups) in natural resource rich, rural and peri-urban areas of Zambia. This will be achieved through the empowerment of Rights Holders (men, women, youth) to hold duty bearers accountable for equitable access to and distribution of national resources. This will be implemented through ten (10) civil society organisations.
The SAP-II is also expected to lead to the following outcomes;
Program Outcome 1: Right holders (RHs), in targeted districts of Zambia are empowered to hold duty bearers accountable for equitable access and distribution of national resources (including natural resources);
Program Outcome 2: Targeted duty bearers (state institutions and corporates) are transparent and are accountable to right holders in the administration and governance of national/natural resources;
Program Outcome 3: Partner organisations have increased capacity to implement their mandates and effectively deliver rights based social, political and economic programmes.
